{"abstract": "A feature makes it easier to save your place in complex books like \u201cA Game of Thrones\u201d while you glance at reference pages with photos, maps or family trees.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/29/technology/amazon-kindle-learns-to-navigate-literary-thickets.html", "snippet": "A feature makes it easier to save your place in complex books like \u201cA Game of Thrones\u201d while you glance at reference pages with photos, maps or family trees.", "lead_paragraph": "SEATTLE \u2014 For years, Amazon has been chiseling away at the irritants that keep many people from switching to e-readers. The company has improved the legibility of the text on Kindle screens to make it nearly indistinguishable from print, and fiddled with the ergonomics of the new Kindle Oasis to make using it feel more like holding a book.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/06/28/business/29KINDLE1/29KINDLE1-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 839, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/06/28/business/29KINDLE1/29KINDLE1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 839}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/06/28/business/29KINDLE1/29KINDLE1-jumbo.jpg", "height": 1024, "width": 733, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/06/28/business/29KINDLE1/29KINDLE1-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 2048, "width": 1466, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/06/28/business/29KINDLE1/29KINDLE1-thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75, "subType": "thumbnail", "crop_name": "thumbStandard", "